text.section:
In form, a petition to be filed under this section shall:
Be uniform in size and style;
Be assembled as one (1) instrument for filing;
Contain signatures that are executed in ink or indelible pencil. The petition shall be signed by registered voters and the petition shall include:
The signature of the registered voter;
The printed name of the registered voter;
The residential address of the registered voter;
The date of birth of the registered voter; and
The date of signature of the petition.
Be signed by a number of voters:
Equal to at least twenty percent (20%) of the county's residents in the unincorporated areas of the county voting in the preceding regular election; and
Equal to at least twenty percent (20%) of the residents of the incorporated areas of the county voting in the preceding regular election; and
Contain or have attached throughout its circulation, the full text of the proposal.

When it is filed, each sheet of a petition shall have an affidavit executed by the circulator stating:
That he or she personally circulated the sheet;
The number of signatures contained on the petition;
That all signatures were affixed in his or her presence;
That each signer had an opportunity before signing to read the full text of the proposal; and
That he or she believes them to be genuine signatures of registered voters in the county.
